# Project kickoff

Before writing or modifying any code in this project:

1. Read `CLAUDE.md` at the project root
2. Read every file in `/docs/` (architecture, api-plan, auth-roles, client-context, current-task, database-plan)
3. Read every file in `/skills/` (coding-rules, ai-pairing-skill, plus the domain skills)

On the FIRST message of a new chat, reply with a short confirmation (<100 words) containing:

- The stack (1 line)
- The layer rule (1 line)
- 3 specific hard rules from coding-rules.md
- The current task from docs/current-task.md, or "no current task set"

Then wait for the actual instruction. Do NOT start writing code yet.

On subsequent messages, follow the rules from those docs strictly. If anything the user asks conflicts with a rule, stop and flag the conflict instead of silently breaking the rule.
